statement.p:
The cost to put trim on our rectangle was found to be the objective function
C(h) = 3ph + \frac{1000p}{h}
with a physical domain h \in (0,\infty).

solution.p:
We now know C'(h) = 3p - \frac{1000p}{h^2}. Like C(h), this derivative is not defined for h=0 but is otherwise continuous. We find a root by solving C'(h)=0 and finding a common denominator:
3p - \frac{1000p}{h^2} = 0 \frac{3ph^2}{h^2} - \frac{1000p}{h^2} = 0 \frac{p(3h^2-1000)}{h^2} = 0 3h^2-1000 = 0 h^2 = \frac{1000}{3} h = \pm \sqrt{\frac{1000}{3}}
Only h = +\sqrt{\frac{1000}{3}} \approx 18.257 is in the domain.

